	* Extension setup routines are divided into the module OpenGLExt.
	* lib/opengl_ext_common.rb (get_extension_enum_symbols, get_extension_command_symbols): Return array of enum/method symbols. Now you can know what symbols will be appended in the OpenGL module before setting up extensions.
	* lib/opengl_ext_common.rb (setup_extension): Added new argument 'skip_check'. You can skip availability check by setting true to 'skip_check'.
	* sample/NamespaceMigration/namespace_gl.rb, etc.: Demonstrates how to modify OpenGL prefix into that of ruby-opengl1/2.

